    "Finally, in a particular but still significant situation, the following proposition holds.Proposition 1.",
    "Assume that m A (t) is analytical.",
    "Suppose that for any fixed w ∈ I the initial distribution f in (A, w) = f (w, A, 0) is even with respect to A.",
    "If a p is given by (4), then m A ≡ 0.Proof.",
    "We want to show that d n dt n m A (t)| t=0 = 0 for all n ∈ N. The symmetry with respect to A of f in (A, w) ensures that m A (0) = 0 and thatd dt m A (t)| t=0 = λ A ω p ∫ R×I ( Ā - 1 2) f in (A, w)dAdw = 0.A simple calculation shows that for all n ≥ 2d n dt n m A (t)| t=0 = λ n A ω n p (2γ) n-1 ∫ I×(-γ,γ) ( Ā -1 2) f in (A, w)dAdw = 0, therefore the result follows."
  ]
}